main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects over Dahlgren, Virginia on various dates in April 1955.
interesting points: Witnesses reported seeing a round object approximately 20-30 feet in diameter, described as silver metallic and moving slowly,Two trained military officers observed an unidentified object traveling at an estimated speed of over 800 knots and at an altitude of approximately 20,000 feet,The security guard from the Marine Proving Ground was among the first to report the sighting,Two bright circular lights were observed overhead flying at high speed without any sound,Objects exhibited erratic flight patterns and were confirmed by ground radar tracking.
sighted object: unidentified flying objects, round and metallic
witness description: military personnel and a security guard from the Marine Proving Ground
